title: American gymnasts create unlikely alliance with Belarus
text:
American gymnasts compete for Belarus - and against their own country at worlds By WILL GRAVES AP Sports Writer   8:08   8:08   
Subjects: 
United Kingdom (463) 

GLASGOW, Scotland — American teenagers Alaina Kwan and Kylie Dickson took an unorthodox path to the world gymnastics championships. 
The two 16-year-olds from southern California came in 73rd and 75th in all-around qualifying while competing for Belarus, a country neither has even visited. 
The eastern European country granted the Americans dual citizenship and nominated them to the world championships hoping their performances could breathe life into a struggling program. 
Nellie Kim of the Belarus Gymnastics Federation defended the decision, pointing out athletes are frequently given dual citizenship in search of better opportunities. 
It's unclear whether the girls will continue to compete for Belarus going forward. Neither qualified for the all-around final next week.
